args:
Luca and the prince fight a hard battle against
Kai Yan. The villain seeks to cull the weakened
prince, but Luca's conviction to stand with his
friend foils his plan. Just then, Gatov and the
others come rushing to the pair's aid, and the
party again prepares to battle Agito's agent.
Dammit! I had a feeling that wouldn't\nbe enough to put this meathead down.
The weak may join their hands together,\nbut weak they remain.
Oh, crap! You ain't ready to fight\nat all, {player_name}!
And since it's just the two of us,\nthis don't look good...
Culling the weak in order of their infirmity.\nThis is the proper order. The way of things.
The axiom is plain: If you protect the weak,\nyou open yourself to greater depths of\ndebility. You must abandon that man.
Such determination is all that will impel\na species to greatness.
Oh, shut the hell up already!\nI'd never abandon my friend!
Do you not yet grasp that you walk\nthe path to dissolution?
Very well. If you wish to die as brothers,\nyou will do so clinging to your own frailty.
I think that's enough of that.
Sorry for running a bit behind, fellowsâ€”\nthough it looks like you held up all right.
And so are all of you!
You certainly took your lumps in protecting\nthe prince, Luca. Let me heal you now.
I'm so glad you're all right, Brother.
But your mana flow is disturbed.\nPray let me take care of that.
This should have you back to your\nold self in no time...
My whole body feels lighter...\nThank you, Zena. You're a lifesaver.
No matter who you might be, when you're\nin trouble, we're all gonna come running!
That's what friends are all about!

You who cannot stand alone avert your
collective gazes from your weakness.
You fraternize with others, clinging to
an unseemly life.
Why do you not realize that your\nself-righteous prattle will only guide\nyour species to annihilation?

The only thing we realize is that YOU are
totally crackedâ€”and now it's time to get
your just rewards for the way you treated
Luca and my darling!
Buddy, I am gettin' REAL damn tired of\nlistenin' to ya ramble on about nothin'.
So now, big man, I'm gonna beat the\npower of friendship right into that meaty\nhead'a yers!
You are a flock of bleating weaklings,\nand I will cull the lot of you as one!
